post_text:
It is with heavy hearts that we are sharing the news that someone a part of our Stamford Academy family has passed away this past Friday. Clare Harding was an amazing, dedicated, hard working volunteer at Stamford Academy for the last 8 years. She was a ray of sunshine in our building who believed in helping our students build the best and brightest future for themselves. She worked tirelessly with seniors on filling out college applications, their FAFSA or organizing their transcripts. She greeted every student and staff member with a smile and would always sneak you a piece of gum if you asked her for it. Mrs. Harding was truly a beautiful soul and she will be missed by so many.

‚ÄúThere are no goodbyes for us. Wherever you are, you will always be in my heart.‚Äù -Gandhi

Mrs. Harding cared deeply about our students education and their futures so let‚Äôs make her proud by continuing to work hard, showing kindness to each other and focusing on our futures. If you need to speak to anyone, please reach out to your family advocate or Dana.

Clare Harding was an amazing, dedicated, hard working volunteer at Stamford Academy for the last 8 years. She was a ray of sunshine in our building who believed in helping our students build the best and brightest future for themselves. She worked tirelessly with seniors on filling out college applications, their FAFSA or organizing their transcripts. She greeted every student and staff member with a smile and would always sneak you a piece of gum if you asked her for it. Mrs. Harding was truly a beautiful soul and she will be missed by so many.

‚ÄúThere are no goodbyes for us. Wherever you are, you will always be in my heart.‚Äù -Gandhi

Mrs. Harding cared deeply about our students education and their futures so let‚Äôs make her proud by continuing to work hard, showing kindness to each other and focusing on our futures. If you need to speak to anyone, please reach out to your family advocate or Dana.

post_text: #TBT to yesterday when thanks to an anonymous donor our whole school was able to go see the movie The Hate U Give! This movie is emotional and so relevant to the lives of many of our students and staff. It sparked many conversations today, across all classes, and it inspired our students to find their voice and decide how they wanted to use it. Thank you to the donor who made this happen! We all enjoyed this amazing film and we loved having an entire theatre to ourselves with popcorn, fruit snacks and a soda! #thehateugive #fieldtrip #useyourvoice #relevant #grateful
